    "text": "The WorldLines paper defines 'translating long-term memory into embodied plans' as a design element of its planner, not as a general fundamental challenge for all agents.",
    "topic": "definitional scope"
  },
  {
    "text": "The paper explicitly states that this translation addresses partial observability and overwritten world states, making it a solution subcomponent rather than a standalone problem.",
    "topic": "problem-solution relation"
  },
  {
    "text": "No section of the WorldLines paper presents memory-to-plan translation as an independently necessary challenge for embodied agents outside the context of its partial observability framework.",
    "topic": "architectural framing"
  },
  {
    "text": "The contradiction arises from interpreting a solution technique as if it were claimed to be a fundamental problem, which the original text does not assert.",
    "topic": "contradiction source"
  }
]
